{"title": "Children's Life of the Bee", "description": "Buzz, buzz, buzz. A fascinating and beautifully written explanation of the life of the honey bee. Maeterlinck, who won the Noble Prize for Literature, wrote a more scholarly work called The Life of the Bee but then rewrote it in simpler terms so that children could appreciate what goes in a hive.  The book describes in simple language the inner workings of a hive from its beginning with a swarm to the fully functional hive with thousands of workers, drones and a queen busily building, repairing and gathering. (Summary by phil chenevert)", "duration": 9730, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2835", "name": "Maurice Maeterlinck"}], "coverArt": "http://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt16/life_bee_1204.jpg", "copyright_year": "1919", "genres": ["Science"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Phil Chenevert"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Phil Chenevert"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Phil Chenevert"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Abigail Rasmussen"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "1 - ON THE THRESHOLD OF THE HIVE", "readers": [5717], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/childrens_lifeofbee_pc_librivox/childrnslifofthebee_1_maeterlinck_64kb.mp3", "duration": 686}, {"section": 2, "title": "2 - THE SWARM", "readers": [5717], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/childrens_lifeofbee_pc_librivox/childrnslifofthebee_2_maeterlinck_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3090}, {"section": 3, "title": "3 - THE FOUNDATION OF THE CITY", "readers": [5717], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/childrens_lifeofbee_pc_librivox/childrnslifofthebee_3_maeterlinck_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2622}, {"section": 4, "title": "4 - THE YOUNG QUEENS", "readers": [5717], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/childrens_lifeofbee_pc_librivox/childrnslifofthebee_4_maeterlinck_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1223}, {"section": 5, "title": "5 - THE MASSACRE OF THE MALES", "readers": [5717], "path": "htt